python correlation coefficient

its explains how much two variables or axix linearly related


Mechanism:

pearson's corr

-1,0,1

-1-------->Negative correlation
1--------->Positive correlation
0---------> Nothing


skewness:

        It is a measure of asymmetry of probability distribution

positive skewness-----> distribution is falling into right side(mean>median>mode)
negative skewness-----> distribution is falling into left side(mean<median<mode)
zero     skewness-----> perfectly symmetrical


kurtosis:


-----> it is the process of 'tailedness'

leptokurtic-----> positive kurtosis

mesokurtic-----> zero

platykurtic-----> negative kurtosis

Exploratory Data Analysis or Data Wrangling